<HEAD>Mayor's Order Rescues Cat From Steamy Death</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SELMA, Ala. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   It took an emergency order from Mayor Joe
Smitherman to save Whitey the cat from a steamy death in the trunk
of a locked car.
   The cat on Tuesday jumped unnoticed into the trunk of the car,
spending six hours trapped in the locked trunk. As mid-day
temperatures soared, the cat's cries grew weaker as frantic
passersby gathered around the car and searched for the car's owner.
   Unable to locate the owner, the president of the local humane
society called the mayor's office with word of the predicament.
Smitherman contacted police and empowered an officer to break into
the car to rescue the cat.
   Drenched in sweat, its body limp, the white female cat was taken
to Selma Animal Hospital, where a veterinarian treated it for heat
stroke. Whitey was later listed in serious but stable condition and
doctors expected it to recover.
