<1ST_LINE>r a PM-JailRiot     06-30 0187</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Jail Riot,0193</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Prisoners Riot at County Jail, Guards Injured</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN ANTONIO, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fights broke out at the county jail as
four captured escapees were being placed in isolation, injuring 10
deputies and seven inmates, authorities said.
   The trouble began about 8:30 p.m. Wednesday, when guards
attempted to move three of the escapees from a large room, where
several inmates are housed, according to guards who spoke on
condition of anonymity.
   The other inmates protested and a fight ensued with prisoners
breaking off furniture and using the broken parts as weapons,
authorities said.
   The riot was put down in 30 minutes and inmates at the Bexar
County Adult Detention Center were locked in cells, authorities
said.
   Guards said at least seven prisoners were injured. Officials at
Santa Rosa Hospital, who declined to give their names, said many of
the guards and prisoners being treated suffered injuries such as
broken fingers and broken hands.
   County Sheriff Harlon Copeland declined to comment about the
disorder.
   The four had escaped from the new $40 million on May 10, using
toenail clippers to cut through a wire fence.
</TEXT>
