<HEAD>Dukakis Picks Up Endorsement from Union of IRS and Customs Workers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Democratic presidential candidate Michael
Dukakis has his first formal union endorsement, from the
59,000-member National Treasury Employees Union.
   The group, which represents mostly federal Internal Revenue
Service and Customs Service workers, said the backing was on
Dukakis' commitment to beef up the Customs Service's drug
interdiction programs and revenue agencies such as the IRS as a way
to reduce the federal deficit.
   ``The Reagan administration has been long on empty words and
false perceptions but very, very short on good deeds,'' the union's
president, Robert Tobias, said Wednesday.
   Tobias also praised what he called Dukakis' commitment to
collective bargaining as evidenced by his relations with
Massachusetts state employees over the past decade.
