<1ST_LINE>r i BC-Vatican-LefebvreText     06-30 0231</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Vatican-Lefebvre Text,0233</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Text of Vatican Statement on Lefebvre</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Rebel Archbishop, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VATICAN CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is the official English-language text
of the Vatican statement on Archbishop Marcel Lefebvre. The
original was issued in Italian.
   ``With regard to rumors voiced in Monsignor Lefebvre circles
concerning the excommunication latae sentetiae (automatic)
mentioned in Canon Law N. 1382, the Vatican Press Office notes that:
   ``According to Canon 1013 (no bishop is allowed to consecrate
another bishop without the explicit papal authorization), the
consecration of bishops on June 30 by Mons. Lefebvre, in spite of
the admonition on June 17, have been carried out explicitly against
the pope's will; this is a formally schismatic act according to
Canon 751, in as much as he openly refused submission to the Holy
Father and communion with the members of the church under his
jurisdiction.
   ``Consequently, both Mons. Lefebvre and the bishops consecrated
by him, Bernard Fellay, Bernard Tissier de Mallerais, Richard
Williamson, Alfonso de Galarreta, have ipso facto incurred
excommunication latae sententiae reserved to the Apostolic See. In
this case Canon 1323 is inapplicable, because the circumstances
mentioned in the canon have not obtained: the so-called `case of
necessity' has been intentionally fabricated by Mons. Lefebvre in
order to maintain an attitude of division within the Catholic
church, notwithstanding the ecclesial communion and the concessions
offered by the Holy Father John Paul II.''
</TEXT>
