<HEAD>Court to Hear Appeal of Texas Man Said to Have Capacity of
7-Year-Old</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Supreme Court today agreed to hear the
appeal of a Texas man sentenced to death who, the justices were
told, has the reasoning capacity of a 7-year-old.
   The justices said they will study arguments that executing
Johnny Paul Penry for the Oct. 25, 1979, killing of Pamela
Carpenter would be ``cruel and unusual punishment'' banned by the
Constitution's Eighth Amendment.
