<HEAD>World's Youngest Transplant Recipient Will Go Home To Canada On
Friday</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Paul Holc will go home to Canada on Friday,
eight months after he became the world's youngest transplant
patient.
   The 8-month-old heart patient has progressed so well since his
surgery Oct. 16 that ``he is going home sooner than the one year we
usually keep the babies,'' said Anita Rockwell, spokeswoman for
Loma Linda University Medical Center.
   Since his transplant, Paul and his parents, Gordon and Alice
Holc, have stayed in a temporary residence near Loma Linda, 60
miles east of Los Angeles. They live in the Vancouver suburb of
Surrey.
   Once home, he will continue to receive medicines to prevent
rejection of the heart he received three hours after birth, Ms.
Rockwell said.
