   The Seattle Archdiocese will assume sponsorship
of Mass for homosexuals, the archbishop announced Thursday, but the
group that had run the ministry is divided over whether to accept
the change or move elsewhere.
   While accepting homosexuals within the church, Archbishop
Raymond G. Hunthausen made clear that ``church teaching rejects
homosexual acts.''
   The Seattle chapter of Dignity, a group for homosexual
Catholics, was evenly split Sunday in a vote on whether to endorse
