past five years, according to a forecast by Standard & Poor's Corp.
   Consumer prices increased less than 4 percent in 1987.
   The Labor Department has reported that inflation ran at an
annual rate of 4.4 percent from January through May. Since 1983,
inflation has risen at an annual rate of between 3 percent and 4
percent.
