<TEXT>
   Led by General Motors Corp., Ford Motor Co. and
Boeing Co., the nation's top exporters had a banner 1987, as a
cheaper dollar pushed overseas sales up and in turn helped chip
away at the trade deficit, Fortune magazine says.
   Exports by Fortune's ``top 50'' rose 8 percent to nearly $80
billion last year, while total U.S. exports jumped 11 percent to
$253 billion, the largest one-year increase this decade, the
magazine said in its July 18 issue.
   Fortune said exports continued to climb this year, reaching $29
billion in March for the highest monthly showing ever.
</TEXT>
