in an erratic session. The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials fell
8.89 to 2,121.98.
   Grain and soybean futures prices tumbled on the Chicago Board of
Trade as showers in the drought-stricken Midwest created panic in
the trading pits and spurred some of the steepest declines in the
exchange's history.
   The dollar rose amid speculation industrialized nations would
not intervene against the currency. Gold prices responded by
falling sharply.
   Bond prices fell in seesaw trading.
