<1ST_LINE>u f BC-AutoProdn     06-30 0167</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Auto Prodn,0175</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Production Down This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
237,016 cars and light trucks this week, down from last week's
241,765, Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   This week's production is higher than the same week a year ago,
in which 109,804 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade
journal said.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 162,152 cars this week,
compared with 159,987 a week ago. Only 80,817 cars were made in the
same week in 1987, when several General Motors Corp. plants were
closed for model changeover and all U.S. plants worked a four-day
week.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 74,864,
compared with last week's 81,778 and last year's 28,987.
   Canadian automakers were to build 20,803 cars this week, down
from 24,200 a week ago but up from last year's 13,286.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 15,451,
compared with 20,447 a week ago and 14,849 in the same week last
year.
