<DOCNO> AP880630-0344 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-06-30-88 2028EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r f AM-American-Marketing     06-30 0155</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-American-Marketing,0163</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>American Airlines Creates New Marketing Division</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   American Airlines has created a new
division responsible for marketing the carrier's operations,
research and consulting skills to other businesses, company
officials said Thursday.
   Donald J. Carty, American's senior vice president for finance
and planning, said the division, called American Airlines Decision
Technologies, is comprised of the airline's former Operations
Research Department.
   Thomas M. Cook, who was the managing director for Operations
Research, will take over the new division.
   ``American Airlines Decision Technologies is an analytical
consulting group that specializes in applying technology to
decision-making,'' Cook said.
   In 1987, the Operations Research division of the airline, under
Cook, obtained a number of notable contracts, including a computer
modeling contract with the Federal Aviation Administration and a
yield management contract with Amtrak.
   Cook said the establishment of the new division will market the
airline's product better and also assist with internal operations.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
